Attributes: Character attributes represent the core qualities of a character.  They generally range from one to six.  \
\
1:	An attribute of one represents a dramatic deficiency, but not crippling.  \
\
2:	The general average rating that most NPC\'92s have is two.  \
\
3-4:	These ratings are common among protagonists and represent a distinctive 	amount of talent and conditioning.\
\
5-6:	The natural pinnacle of human ability.  Ratings of six are generally only possible 	with paranormal ability, and typically further augmented by special powers.\
\
Might:	The character\'92s physical strength and resistance. This attribute is generally tied to Athletics and Melee.  It is important to the derived attribute of Vitality.\
\
Agility: The character\'92s grace and reflexes.  This attribute is tied to Firearms and Stealth.  It is important to derived attributes of Melee Defense and Initiative.\
\
Intuition: The character\'92s instinct and ability to notice details.  This attribute is tied to Empathy, Nature, and Streetwise.\
\
Wits: The character\'92s intellectual creativity and ability to think on her feat.  This attribute is tied to Academics, Occult, and Tinker.\
\
Presence: The character\'92s strength of personality and social tact.  This attribute is tied to Composure and Persuade.\
\
Skills:  These \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
