The first rank in a skill is \'93proficient,\'94 which grants the character basic understanding and training in the skill.  Proficiency gives the character a +3 to rolls involving that skill.\
\
The second rank in a skill is \'93experienced,\'94 which represents additional practice and more advanced training.  Experience grants a character an additional +2 (+5 total) to rolls involving the skill, and a single basic knack.  Character who are experienced in a skill can learn additional knacks as a form of advancement at any minor milestone.\
\
The third rank in a skill is \'93mastery,\'94 which grants a character a additional +1 (+6 total) to rolls involving the skill, as well as single master knack.  Mastery can only be acquired through advancement in a major milestone. Additional master knacks can be acquired at any major milestone.\
